(2, 278, 'Clark Aaron', 'aclark@hotmail.com', '', '79.114.120.6', '2015-10-20 16:52:29', '2015-10-20 16:52:29', 'The sight is everything I wanted it to be! It is just a gorgeous piece of history and architecture. Go over it, go under it, drive across it, and bike around it; it will not disappoint.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(3, 278, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-22 12:20:07', '2015-10-22 12:20:07', 'For strange high level views over London this is a great place. If you are a person interested in how the bridge moves aside for shipping this is a must. The inside offers viewing of the previous hydraulic mechanisms, a tribute to Victorian and early 20th century engineering.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(4, 297, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-22 12:23:50', '2015-10-22 12:23:50', 'If you get a chance, this is a must while in London it gives you a great view of the city on a clear day. I recommend going very early or buying a fast pass as the lines can be long through out the day.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(5, 297, 'Alin', 'bluesky_c3@yahoo.com', '', '79.114.43.127', '2015-10-30 14:22:59', '2015-10-30 14:22:59', 'Even though it was a little misty I would not have missed this ride for the world. It was fascinating. We paid a little extra when we booked online so that we didn''t have to stand in the queue for too long which was well worth it.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(6, 645, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-26 08:26:22', '2015-10-26 08:26:22', 'Agree it is not the cheapest especially with a service charge of 12.5 recent that we weren''t aware off. That said the quality of the food was absolutely amazing. Such gorgeous imaginative cakes. High standard of service. One of our party had hot chocolate and everyone wished they had had it. Hot chocolate in a pot with the most amazing selection of accompaniments. Never seen that before and just loved it. Thanks to all the staff for making our afternoon so special.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(7, 645, 'Jacob', 'jacob@listable.com', '', '154.122.41.11', '2015-12-09 20:45:29', '2015-12-09 20:45:29', 'Agree it is not the cheapest especially with a service charge of 12.5 recent that we weren’t aware off. That said the quality of the food was absolutely amazing. Such gorgeous imaginative cakes. High standard of service. One of our party had hot chocolate and everyone wished they had had it. Hot chocolate in a pot with the most amazing selection of accompaniments. Never seen that before and just loved it. Thanks to all the staff for making our afternoon so special.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(8, 646, 'Julie', 'r5forlife@hotmail.com', '', '207.224.193.74', '2015-11-18 20:25:16', '2015-11-18 20:25:16', 'Loved the food. Loved the service. Loved everything about it.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(9, 666, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 13:36:30', '2015-11-06 13:36:30', 'I was in London last week and my friend who lives there told me to meet her at Pizza East for Sunday brunch! I said, "Pizza?!" I really want brunch! She said, "Trust me on this one!" I''m so glad that I did! Amazing avocado-toast with eggs. But I''m so glad I had the pizza too! With all due respects to Nancy Silverton at Mozza in Los Angeles, this pizza trumps hers! (and I love hers!!) This is better. "Trust me on this one!"', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(10, 666, 'Ilinca', 'ilincaroman@gmail.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-12-09 14:53:58', '2015-12-09 14:53:58', 'I wanna start off saying that I have been eating here for over four years. I highly recommend this restaurant to everybody. Don''t just take my word for it.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(11, 666, 'Vlad', 'vlad.olaru@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-12-09 14:56:11', '2015-12-09 14:56:11', 'This is a family run Pizzeria and restaurant. The service is always friendly and warm. The menu is extensive and they will cook to order where they can. The Risotto''s are delicious, we take away and eat in.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(12, 666, 'Matt', 'mgmatthews18@gmail.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-12-09 15:00:38', '2015-12-09 15:00:38', 'You need to lift your game for regulars to continue dining here. First impressions count. The service is a huge let down along with just now ordinary food. Such a shame as this was one of our favourite local restaurants.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(13, 753, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-26 08:22:57', '2015-10-26 08:22:57', 'If you''re one who loves art, culture, quirky, special clothing, household wares, design, this is THE place! Look no more. You won''t be disappointed. Love how the whole store is curated!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(14, 753, 'Olivia', 'olivia@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-11 13:14:55', '2015-11-11 13:14:55', 'Visited here on my own while waiting for a friend and it was an absolute find!\nNot only do they do delicious homemade food but there is also a fantastic little shop inside selling all sorts of old and interesting vintage stuff. It was the perfect place to sit and relax and wait for an hour, free wifi for an hour and lovely staff.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(15, 467, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2016-01-06 13:21:40', '2016-01-06 13:21:40', 'This was my first time staying in this hotel. I love being on Park Lane and usually stay at either The Four Seasons or The Dorchester but I was looking for a bit more space than the typical hotel room this trip. The Grosvenor House Apartments was the perfect answer.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(16, 520, 'Alin', 'alin.clamba@yahoo.com', '', '79.114.105.76', '2015-10-22 18:51:04', '2015-10-22 18:51:04', 'I grew up in the area and Greenwich Park was my playground as a kid. I love this park all times of the year.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(17, 671, 'Manuel', 'test@gmail.com', '', '72.220.23.161', '2015-11-22 21:46:42', '2015-11-22 21:46:42', 'I had the opportunity of visiting this amazing place and let me tell you it is far the best places to visit on Earth...', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(18, 739, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-26 08:21:32', '2015-10-26 08:21:32', 'It is a great place to dream and wander. It''s sumptuous and decadent. Service as ever outstanding — lovely girl wrapped each gift —  It''s Liberty and you can''t help but feel special just being there ??', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(19, 279, 'George Olaru', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-22 12:17:30', '2015-10-22 12:17:30', 'Really enjoyed this, lots of information and the guide really knew his stuff (especially about Arsenal)', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(20, 441, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-11 15:21:57', '2015-11-11 15:21:57', 'One of the best bars in London in terms of location/features and most importantly, price! Nice decor all over with modern furnitures and laid back fireplace in combination with chilled lighting.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(21, 569, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 13:27:37', '2015-11-06 13:27:37', 'Stayed here for a few days in half term. With a trip to the theatre to see Lion King. The hotel was perfectly situated for all the London things we wanted to do. All the hotel staff were so friendly and helpful. We were on the sixth floor this blocked out a lot of traffic noise, as London never sleeps.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22, 569, 'Barki', 'barki@gmail.com', '', '83.128.190.249', '2015-11-16 15:56:22', '2015-11-16 15:56:22', 'Haven''t had any such a great service ever!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(23, 1007, 'Vlad Olaru', 'vlad.olaru@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-13 10:07:43', '2015-11-13 10:07:43', 'Attendant Cafe is the perfect pitstop in central London, away from the hustle & bustle. Nestled underground in a converted loo, the coffee is lovely, the cakes are scrumptious, and the surroundings are an experience second to none! It''s cosy, intimate atmosphere make for an ideal recharge cafe without the roar of the yuppy shopping crowds that you''ll find in nearby cafes. I always have time for a cappuccino and a brownie in the attendant!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(24, 95, 'John', 'alin.clamba@yahoo.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 13:41:28', '2015-11-06 13:41:28', 'The menu is fairly long and complex — be sure to read every last corner, as you might miss something delicious (e.g. Boudin Blanc).', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(25, 123, 'Alex', 'alex.sava@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 17:18:57', '2015-11-06 17:18:57', 'After failing to get a table at a nearby restaurant we wanted to try, a colleague and I chanced upon TED. A short walk from Kings Cross, and what a find. The atmosphere was great, not too noisy so conversation was easy. Tables not crammed together, staff great. The menu was not too extensive and featured seasonal ingredients, always a good sign. Couldn''t believe the prices, incredible value.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(26, 419, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-22 12:28:29', '2015-10-22 12:28:29', 'Perfect location! Modern, pleasant room, good  choice of food in bar area. Location and the apartment was comfortable, spacious with a great terrace and view.  Staff were lovely, very helpful nothing was too much trouble', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(27, 729, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-10-26 08:19:43', '2015-10-26 08:19:43', 'First class service and great modern Italian food. My pal and I had lunch here and despite the place buzzing on a Friday and very busy. Lovely room, modern, stylish decor, this place has just got it ''right'' and delivers a smart, professional and delicious dining experience. Recommended!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(28, 833, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 17:15:10', '2015-11-06 17:15:10', 'Normally in London I stay at boutique hotels, but I had several business appointemnts and needed a more "appropriate" business venue. This hotel, simply put, was a delight. LARGE roooms, great views, attentive service without being obnoxious or solicitous. Not much to look at from the outside, but this hotel is just wonderful and I will stay there from now on when in London.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(29, 864, 'Alin', 'alin.clamba@yahoo.com', '', '79.114.43.127', '2015-10-30 18:29:17', '2015-10-30 18:29:17', 'This was a really good way to see London. 21st birthday treat. Great combination of sightseeing and speed. Recommended!! Great banter from guide Rory and excellent side dips at speed from Nick. Great trip guys! Thanks!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(30, 1013, 'Vlad Olaru', 'vlad.olaru@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-13 10:36:56', '2015-11-13 10:36:56', 'Despite having lived practically next door for the past year, i''ve only recently visited this lovely eatery. I''ve definitely been missing out. Charm, style, good food, excellent service and a real commitment in supporting various charities and the local community have made The Haberdashery my new favourite local.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(31, 118, 'Serban', 'serban.costandache@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 17:27:14', '2015-11-06 17:27:14', 'This is a very small intimate restaurant and the food service and ambiance are excellent.We enjoyed all the food served from quite a small open kitchen area and would certainly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting the area.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(32, 128, 'Michael', 'michael@pixelgrade.com', '', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 17:12:39', '2015-11-06 17:12:39', 'I took my girlfriend to Jago for her birthday on a colleague''s recommendation and it was a great evening. The space itself is really cool and the service was friendly and accommodating. The food was excellent and surprisingly affordable considering the location and quality of the restaurant as a whole.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(33, 791, 'George', 'george.olaru@pixelgrade.com', 'http://pixelgrade.com', '5.2.190.30', '2015-11-06 13:31:20', '2015-11-06 13:31:20', 'SCP is the kind of place that most of us will never buy anything from but will nonetheless enjoy roaming through the store. Furniture in here is so stylish it would only suit a very specific style of house and a very full wallet for that matter!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(34, 801, 'henry stainton', 'henry@tihh.co.uk', '', '213.133.138.5', '2015-11-18 10:34:17', '2015-11-18 10:34:17', 'Along with office buildings and residential apartments, Paddington Central is also home to a gym, a number of quick lunch stops cafes as well as several canal side bars and restaurants. Enjoy a lunchtime run along Regent’s Canal, an almost traffic-free jog through the heart and soul of London.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
