(91, 1, '2015-10-12 14:27:46', '2015-10-12 14:27:46', '<div class="how-main">\r\n<h2>How It Works</h2>\r\nMeal Blvd is in the business of human connection. While we recognize the importance of food and space, what brings these elements to life is the human touch. Meal Blvd facilitates connection between food lovers that want to entertain and those that seek to experience.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="how_it_works_sec">\r\n<div class="how-img-text">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 img_sec1">\r\n<div class="how-img-img wow slideInLeft animated"  data-wow-duration="1000ms" data-wow-delay="300ms"><img class="img-responsive alignleft wp-image-11169 size-full" src="http://mealblvd.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/howitworks-1.png" alt="howitworks-1" width="352" height="283" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 how-text-text">\r\n<h2>1. Browse</h2>\r\nFlip through our friendly hosts and enchanting spaces. Whatever the occasion, our hosts are looking to provide a dining experience that caters to your needs. Whether you’re in the mood for a mere bowl of soup or an extensive ethnic dish, our diverse selection of hosts will serve your desire.\r\n\r\n<a href="[siteurl]/listings">See How a Claimed Listings Looks</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="how-img-text">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 img_sec1">\r\n<div class="how-img-img-right wow slideInRight animated"  data-wow-duration="1000ms" data-wow-delay="300ms"><img class="img-responsive alignright wp-image-11174 size-full" src="http://mealblvd.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/howitworks-2.png" alt="howitworks-2" width="346" height="262" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 how-text-text">\r\n<h2>2. Book a Meal</h2>\r\nChat with a host to arrange meal plans. It can be last minute meal plans or a momentous event, months in the planning; our hosts are always here to make your dining experience one to remember.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="how-img-text">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 img_sec1">\r\n<div class="how-img-img wow slideInLeft animated"  data-wow-duration="1000ms" data-wow-delay="300ms"><img class="img-responsive alignleft wp-image-11176 size-full" src="http://mealblvd.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/howitworks-3.png" alt="howitworks-3" width="348" height="255" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-6 how-text-text">\r\n<h2>3. Enjoy</h2>\r\nBreak bread and share with others outside the norm. Each space is different, each host and guest is different, but this is where excitement exists. When you embark on your meal experience with Meal Blvd, you never know what you might discover.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="how-bottom-main">\r\n            <h5>Ready to reach all of the people who matter most to your business?</h5>\r\n         <a class="btn fullwidth" href="#">Add Your Listing Now</a>\r\n        </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 'Chefs and Foodies together one meal', 'Find great places to eat and connect with great minds.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-it-works', '', '', '2016-09-27 04:42:53', '2016-09-27 04:42:53', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?page_id=91', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2015-09-07 09:15:25', '2015-09-07 09:15:25', 'Set in Knightsbridge, award-winning Bar Boulud, London is a French-inspired bistro and wine bar at Mandarin Oriental Hyde Park, under the direction of renowned Lyon-born chef Daniel Boulud. The full à la carte menu, served Monday through Saturday and Sunday evenings, is based on seasonal, rustic French cooking with an array of charcuterie specially prepared onsite, as well as Boulud’s popular American transplants, the “Yankee”, “Piggie” and signature “BB Burger”.\n\nAs an excellent option for pre-theatre dining, Bar Boulud offers a £17 two course or £19 three course ‘Bouchon Menu’, changing weekly Monday to Friday, available until 7pm. New to 2015, Bar Boulud is now serving Sunday brunch from 11am to 3.30pm at £39.', 'Bar Boloud', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'bar-boloud', '', '', '2015-09-07 09:15:25', '2015-09-07 09:15:25', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=95', 0, 'job_listing', '', 1),
(101, 1, '2015-02-25 08:06:11', '2015-10-13 12:41:12', 'Boasting a spectacular spiral staircase clad in Gaucho’s signature cowhide, the restaurant is split over two floors. The impressive ground floor dining area is flooded with light from the soaring arched windows of this beautiful building, while the upstairs gallery is a glittering display of white leather and glass tables.\n\nDuring the week, lawyers and locals have lunch under the sparkling chandeliers. On weekend evenings, a chic crowd settles in to the boutique mezzanine lounge bar: an inviting hideaway after the sun sets.', 'Roast Chancery Lane', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'roast-chancery-lane', '', '', '2015-02-25 08:06:11', '2015-10-13 12:41:12', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=101', 0, 'job_listing', '', 0),
(113, 1, '2015-05-14 09:19:23', '2015-10-13 12:55:52', '<div class="content__main--half">\n\nCombining Peru’s exciting cuisine with Soho’s spark, Ceviche Soho kick-started London’s Peruvian restaurant revolution. We take excellence in Peruvian food and drink very seriously. Ceviche made in front of you at our Ceviche Bar, fresh as you can get.\n\n</div>\n<div class="content__main--half">\n\nSuperfood salads, sizzling barbecued anticuchos and a Pisco Sour or three at our Pisco Bar. It’s all served up with a healthy portion of ‘chicha’ on the side. Chicha? It’s a Lima thing. It means cheeky or playful and it shimmies through everything we do.\n\n</div>', 'Ceviche Soho', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ceviche-soho', '', '', '2015-05-14 09:19:23', '2015-10-13 12:55:52', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=113', -1, 'job_listing', '', 0),
(118, 1, '2015-09-23 17:20:03', '2015-09-23 17:20:03', '‘A place to share simple and honest food’? Well, Paesan at Exmouth Market sure don’t let on that there is something very extraordinary about them. Serving you true Italian peasant dishes, lovingly prepared and created, and in a most inspiring place.\n\nPaesan were nominated for Restaurant &amp; Bar Awards as well as shortlisted for menu of the year, doing it all with the simple yet magic formula of aperitivo, small plates, pasta, carne and pesce.', 'Paesan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'paesan', '', '', '2015-09-23 17:20:03', '2015-09-23 17:20:03', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=118', -1, 'job_listing', '', 1),
(123, 1, '2015-09-11 13:26:40', '2015-09-11 13:26:40', 'Think.Eat.Drink was established in 2009 by Jamie Grainger-Smith, with the vision of developing a specialised consultancy dedicated to helping companies in the food and drinks industry be more forward-thinking and environmentally aware.\r\n\r\nIt provides guidance, advice and support on many different levels, ranging from food and drink menus, vision, strategies, sustainable design and advice, waste strategies to ethical suppliers and procurement. We have a broad range of experience managing change across a variety of organisations.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pan fried fillet of sea bream with soft fennel and fresh herb dressing, cucumber and sesame</li>\r\n	<li>Herb marinated Scottish beef fillet with roasted red pepper, salsa verde, broccoli</li>\r\n	<li>Pearl barley risotto with porcini and truffled herb mascarpone.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor drinks, there''ll be a strong focus on biodynamic, carbon-neutral and traditional wines, organic spirits and mixers and plenty of cocktails.', 'Think Eat Drink', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'think-eat-drink', '', '', '2016-09-28 10:37:37', '2016-09-28 10:37:37', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?job_listing=t-e-d-47-51-caledonian-road-london-n1-9bu-8-t-e-d', 0, 'job_listing', '', 1),
(128, 1, '2015-09-24 17:26:04', '2015-09-24 17:26:04', 'Dishes are loosely based on Jewish cooking from the Middle East and Europe. Loosely, as a ‘Russian salad’ wouldn’t be recognised by its creator, Belgian chef Lucien Olivier, or many of his antecedents. Instead, whole green beans, large chunks of carrot, peas and potatoes were very lightly dressed with mayonnaise, and all the better for it.\r\n\r\nThe best dish was a veal cheek goulash, served with orzo and a green harissa topping; full-flavoured meat, well-spiced with paprika. Other dishes were lacklustre. Under-grilled fennel let down one offering; a heaped plate of lentils was too monotonous in another — Guy Dimond', 'Jago Food', '', 'expired', 'open', 'closed', '', 'jago', '', '', '2016-09-21 00:08:11', '2016-09-21 00:08:11', '', 0, 'https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=128', 0, 'job_listing', '', 1),
